article.headline: South Dakota State routs Omaha 86-64
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Deondre Parks scored a career-best 26 points as South Dakota State routed Omaha 86-64 on Wednesday night. Parks finished with 7-of-8 shooting from the field -- including 5-of-5 from 3-point range -- for the Jackrabbits (16-7, 7-2 Summit League). Jake Bittle added 21 points and seven rebounds and Cody Larson had 15 points and seven rebounds. The team hit 56.5 percent from the field overall -- including 10 of 20 (50 percent) from distance -- and 82.8 percent from the line. Parks sank a trio of 3-pointers early in the first period, helping the Jackrabbits to a 23-10 lead. They were up 41-31 at the break. A Larson dunk made it 50-33 early in the second half and a Skyler Flatten 3-pointer with 11:43 left extended the Jackrabbits' lead to 62-41 and they cruised to the win. Mike Rostampour led the Mavericks (8-12, 2-6) with 18 points and 11 boards.
